{"type":"message","id":"f0922741","parentId":"b686c11c","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:15:03.529Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-02 11:15 GMT+8] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: If I have a GitHub project that needs your help, what's your recommended workflow? How should I set it up so you can effectively work on it while respecting the OpenClaw security boundaries?"}],"timestamp":1772421303528}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9552b01","parentId":"f0922741","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:15:24.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll outline the recommended workflow for working with GitHub projects in OpenClaw while respecting security boundaries.\n\n## Recommended GitHub Project Workflow\n\n### 1. **Local Repository Setup**\n- Clone your GitHub repository to your local machine within or accessible to your OpenClaw workspace\n- Ensure you have proper Git credentials configured (SSH keys or personal access tokens)\n- Keep sensitive credentials outside the repository (use `.gitignore` for config files with secrets)\n\n### 2. **Authentication & Permissions**\n- Use GitHub CLI (`gh`) which should be pre-installed on your system\n- Authenticate with `gh auth login` - this creates secure token storage\n- For private repositories, ensure your GitHub account has appropriate access\n- Never store GitHub tokens directly in code or configuration files\n\n### 3. **Working Within Security Boundaries**\n- **Read operations**: OpenClaw can freely read your local repository files and use `gh` CLI to fetch issues, PRs, and repository information\n- **Write operations**: Code modifications happen locally first - you maintain control over what gets committed/pushed\n- **External actions**: Any pushes, PR creation, or GitHub API writes require your explicit approval\n\n### 4. **Typical Workflow Steps**\n\n**For bug fixes or feature development:**\n1. You describe the issue or desired change\n2. I examine your local codebase using file reading tools\n3. I propose specific changes with exact file paths and modifications\n4. You review the proposed changes before I implement them locally\n5. You decide when to commit and push changes\n\n**For issue triage and management:**\n1. I can fetch and analyze GitHub issues using the `gh-issues` skill\n2. I can help prioritize, categorize, or suggest solutions\n3. I can create draft PRs locally but won't push without your approval\n\n### 5. **Available GitHub Tools**\n- **`gh` CLI integration**: Full access to GitHub's official CLI tool\n- **`gh-issues` skill**: Automated issue fetching, analysis, and PR creation workflows\n- **File manipulation**: Precise editing of code files with before/after verification\n- **Code review**: Analysis of existing code, suggestions for improvements\n\n### 6. **Security Best Practices**\n- All file operations occur in your designated workspace directory\n- No automatic pushing to remote repositories\n- Sensitive operations (deletions, external communications) require explicit confirmation\n- GitHub tokens are accessed through secure `gh` CLI storage, not direct file access\n\n### 7. **Getting Started Example**\n```bash\n# In your terminal\ncd /path/to/your/project\ngh auth login  # if not already authenticated\n```\n\nThen you can ask me to:\n- \"Review this GitHub issue and suggest a fix\"\n- \"Help me implement feature X in my project\"\n- \"Analyze my codebase for potential improvements\"\n- \"Create a pull request for these changes\"\n\nWould you like me to help you set up a specific GitHub project or demonstrate any part of this workflow?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":11034,"output":623,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11657,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772421303529}}
